        "body": "Problem\r\n\r\nIn the HTTP service tests, logs were showing \"Nil Correlation ID\" because the tests were using a no-op tracer. Since no real tracer was configured, no valid TraceID values were generated during test execution. This made the test logs less clear and prevented proper validation of tracing behavior.\r\n\r\nSolution\r\n\r\nThe tests have been updated to use a real OpenTelemetry tracer provider. Specifically, go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk/trace is now configured as the TracerProvider in pkg/gofr/service/new_test.go. This ensures that valid TraceIDs are created during tests and that the tracing logic is fully exercised.\r\n\r\nImprovements\r\n\r\nTest logs now contain meaningful correlation IDs instead of \"Nil Correlation ID\".\r\n\r\nTracing behavior is validated more accurately during tests.\r\n\r\nRemoved outdated TODO comments related to this issue.\r\n\r\nBreaking Changes\r\n\r\nNone.\r\n\r\nAdditional Information\r\n\r\nThis change improves the clarity, reliability, and observability of HTTP service tests without impacting runtime behavior.",
